{
  "name": "Lava Release Scorching Stream Rock",
  "type": "spell",
  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Yoton.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p> You coat your hand in Lava release Chakra as you punch forward creating a super-heated shockwave with enough heat to melt rock. <br />All creatures structures and constructs in a 60 feet long, 5 feet wide line directly in front of you must succeed a Dexterity saving throw taking 8d8 Fire damage on a failed save and gaining the burned and corroded condition. <br />On a successful save, you instead deal half damage. <br />All Structures that are destroyed by this jutsu melt becoming a molting pool of fluid that acts like Lava. <br />Its space becomes difficult terrain. <br />A creature that attempts to move through the affected space takes 2d10 Fire damage and gains the burned and corroded conditions. </p><p><br />At Higher Ranks: For each rank you cast this jutsu above B-Rank, increase the cost of the jutsu by 3, and damage by 2d8.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
